+# CTO Incident - phase 7.10.z backlog replenishment block
+
+Saved: 2026-05-08T00:50:08Z. Role: codex-incident-remediation-FR.
+
+## Classification
+
+Infra-only and still valid. The blocked worker output is backlog-planning
+metadata, not a scientific-result change, and the worker reported successful
+local validation. The block is still valid because the blocked branch remains
+non-fast-forward against current `origin/main` and therefore is not
+chef-mergeable.
+
+This is not stale-after-fix. A prior remediation worker recorded a similar
+diagnosis on its branch, but this checkout does not contain that `cto/OUTBOX`
+note on `origin/main`; this note re-preserves the GLASSBOX record for the
+active block.
+
+## Active Block
+
+- Block file: `outbox/_blocks/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z.block`
+- Blocked phase: `phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z`
+- Worker target repo: `/mnt/c/doctorat/bsebench-org/bsebench-async-codex`
+- Worker branch: `origin/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z`
+- Worker SHA: `f2fbb3f830ed197e904b5a45d62bc64f79d500b3`
+- Block creation: `2026-05-08T02:04:38+02:00`
+- Panel average: `81`
+- Advisor artifact: `ADVISOR_CHECK.md` is absent for this phase. The block file
+  records `advisor=BLOCK`; the live chef log records `advisor codex exit
+  non-zero` immediately before block creation.
+
+## Root Cause
+
+Chef attempted to fast-forward merge
+`phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z` into `main` at
+`2026-05-08T01:58:55+02:00`. The branch was based on merge base
+`dd906caaba88a4bc81978bac52370a603484549f`, while `origin/main` had advanced
+through later async state commits. `git merge-base --is-ancestor origin/main
+origin/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z` returns
+exit `1`, and the reverse ancestry check also returns exit `1`.
+
+Chef therefore aborted with `fatal: Not possible to fast-forward, aborting.`
+The panel correctly treated the stale/non-linear branch as a source-of-truth
+pinning failure. The advisor process then failed closed, and chef created the
+block file.
+
+Secondary operational evidence: worker and chef logs show repeated transient
+`index.lock` contention in `/mnt/c/doctorat/bsebench-org/bsebench-async-codex`
+during this period. The latest direct `ls` check did not find a persistent
+`index.lock`, so the live blocker is branch lineage, not an enduring lock file.
+
+## Blast Radius
+
+- One active block pauses normal chef progress across the async clones.
+- The pacer correctly stopped ordinary scientific queueing and queued bounded
+  block-remediation work at `2026-05-08T02:10:09+02:00` and again at
+  `2026-05-08T02:50:08+02:00`.
+- The blocked branch adds only six new backlog BRIEFs:
+  - `cto/AUTONOMY_BACKLOG/phase-7-10-q-runner-hinf-evidence-audit-matrix-ci/BRIEF.md`
+  - `cto/AUTONOMY_BACKLOG/phase-7-10-r-stats-hinf-fragility-bootstrap-sidecar/BRIEF.md`
